  "title": "工作记忆容量一般与项目复杂性无关",
  "image_width": 977,
  "content": "<p data-pid=\"Ism2BT0S\">字母的数量是阿拉伯数字的两倍以上，所以你可能认为，我们能记住的数字串，长度是字母串的两倍。但事实上，典型的<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//notes.andymatuschak.org/z4omDTWHCLoqW7PLpN2tiW63QzoYN5tqxPT9B\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">工作记忆容量</a>大约是{六}个字母和{七}个数字（Crannell 和 Parrish，1957）。</p><p data-pid=\"0ftWsdp5\">见：<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//notes.andymatuschak.org/z75gWU7QuiB5L3x6zFGLGQk3fVkuVJ6eKuEwP\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">人类认知中的「组块」</a><sup data-text=\"人类认知中的「组块」\" data-url=\"http://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/419172087\" data-draft-node=\"inline\" data-draft-type=\"reference\" data-numero=\"1\">[1]</sup></p><hr/><h2>参考文献</h2><p data-pid=\"vNpSQdCI\">Crannell, C. W., &amp; Parrish, J. M. (1957). A Comparison of Immediate Memory Span for Digits, Letters, and Words. The Journal of Psychology, 44(2), 319–327. <a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//doi.org/10.1080/00223980.1957.9713089\" class=\" external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><span class=\"invisible\">https://</span><span class=\"visible\">doi.org/10.1080/0022398</span><span class=\"invisible\">0.1957.9713089</span><span class=\"ellipsis\"></span></a></p><p data-pid=\"wxKykeRM\">Miller, G. A. (1956). The magical number seven, plus or minus two: some limits on our capacity for processing information. <i>Psychological Review</i>, <i>63</i>(2), 81–97. <a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//doi.org/10.1037/h0043158\" class=\" external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><span class=\"invisible\">https://</span><span class=\"visible\">doi.org/10.1037/h004315</span><span class=\"invisible\">8</span><span class=\"ellipsis\"></span></a> <a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//notes.andymatuschak.org/zjfsd9pyxWQAF3HU5k7RAXhRjJBqtMEGKK27\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Miller - The magical number seven, plus or minus two</a></p><h2>链接至本文（已汉化）</h2><ul><li data-pid=\"9m7Mhwgd\"><a href=\"http://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/419172087\" class=\"internal\">人类认知中的「组块」</a></li><li data-pid=\"hNgEYB0P\"><a href=\"http://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/462011439\" class=\"internal\">人类的信道容量随着每个组块的比特量的增加而增加</a></li></ul><h2>声明</h2><p data-pid=\"EXe-X8pe\">此内容发布由 Andy Matuschak 许可。未经允许，不得转载或修改。保留所有权利。</p><p class=\"ztext-empty-paragraph\"><br/></p><blockquote data-pid=\"AuHAS5KY\"><a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//paratranz.cn/projects/3131\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Thoughts Memo</a> 汉化组译制<br/>原文：<a href=\"https://link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//notes.andymatuschak.org/z6Pe8LaXhDBjjiiVX1Y2WJquaZyRQPTJB3y2K\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Working memory span is mostly independent of item complexity (andymatuschak.org)</a></blockquote>",
